## Troubleshooting

- **400 "Only PDF files are supported"** — Upload a `.pdf` file. Other formats are not yet supported.
- **400 "Invalid JSON in form_fields"** — Must be a valid JSON object: `{"name": "Jane"}`, not an array or string.
- **429 "Monthly page quota exceeded"** — Upgrade to PRO or wait until next billing cycle.
- **Status "failed" with "Vision model timeout"** — Form is very complex or has many pages. Try splitting into sections.
- **Fields not mapped correctly** — Use descriptive key names: `"applicant_full_name"` not `"field1"`.
- **Some fields flagged for review** — Expected for 2-5% of fields. Check `report.fields` for the `reason`.
- **Unmapped keys in report** — Your JSON keys didn't match form fields. Check `unmapped_user_keys`.

---

## Help the Developer

- **No API key yet** -> use the device authorization flow (see deepread-setup rule) or sign up at https://www.deepread.tech/dashboard
- **Fill a form** -> POST /v1/form-fill with `file` + `form_fields`, show code in their language
- **Check results** -> GET /v1/form-fill/{job_id}, look at `filled_form_url` and `report`
- **Prevent duplicates** -> use `idempotency_key` parameter
- **Real-time updates** -> set up `webhook_url`, build receiver endpoint
- **Hitting errors** -> check API key, plan limits, file format, JSON validity
- **Review workflow** -> filter fields by `hil_flag: true`, check `reason` for each
- **Batch processing** -> loop with `idempotency_key` per submission, poll all jobs
